Place the spinach, the stock cube and 300ml/Â½ pint of water into a pan over a medium heat. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and cook gently for 2-3 minutes, until the spinach is tender.Season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper and stir in the cream and nutmeg.Blend the soup with a hand blender until smooth.To serve, ladle the soup into a warmed bowl and serve with crusty bread.